race.comment: Sydney-trained SWEET TWILIGHT (12) is still a Maiden but brings narrow defeats from Kembla Grange and Newcastle over 1800m last time. Draws low today and Jay Ford is here to renew his association with the filly. The form stacks right up, and the step up to the middle distance is ideal. DOC MARCH (2) won an Albury Maiden three back by a space and has been nudged out his two since over 1800m at Wagga. The gate is awkward but he peaks today and Penza will give him every chance. Tougher sorting the remainder. HARD GRUNT (5) is still a Maiden but is going well enough to go into the trifecta. Worked home in good style over a mile at Moruya following a narrow defeat over this distance at Queanbeyan. STORMZINO (11) is seasoned and ready for the middle distance. The yard is persevering and it won't surprise to see more from her.
